suncertify.db.impl
Class EngineServiceImpl

java.lang.Object
  suncertify.db.impl.EngineServiceImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
EngineService
public class EngineServiceImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements EngineService

An EngineService for creating engines for local database files, locating remote database engines exported to RMI registries using interface RemoteEngine, and uses RMINetworkService as an engine network service.

Call for getEngine(java.io.File) will return the same engine instance for passed database file. If Engine.shutdown() is called, a new instance will be created if the same database file is passed again.

Local database files can only be created for supported files defined in enum EngineServiceImpl.DBFileType.

Author:
Mohammad S. Abdellatif
See Also:
RMINetworkService, RemoteEngine

getEngine

public Engine getEngine(java.io.File dbFile)
                 throws EngineServiceException
Returns the cached Engine instance for database file dbFile or creates and caches a new one. If the holder for returned instance calls shutdown() on it the cached instance will be deleted and a new one will be created if the same dbFile is passed again to this method.

Specified by:

Parameters:

Returns:
engine for database file.
Throws:
EngineServiceException - if creation for engine is failed.

getEngine

public Engine getEngine(java.lang.String host,
                        int port,
                        java.lang.String serviceName)
                 throws EngineServiceException
Locates a remote database engine exported to RMI registry.

The lookup result for a stub of type RemoteEngine on machine host on port port with name serviceName will be wrapped with an Engine instance which will navigate all calls to stub.

Specified by:
